<!-- Label Studio config for direct mask annotation of yardlines + sidelines.

Workflow:
  1. UNet's predicted mask comes pre-loaded as the active brush layer.
  2. Press F (yardline) or G (sideline) to switch active label.
  3. Use the BRUSH tool to add missing pixels along a line.
  4. Use the ERASER (toggle in toolbar, or hotkey E) to remove wrong pixels.
  5. Adjust brush size with [ and ] (or via the toolbar).

Direct mask editing — what you paint IS the training mask. No polyline → mask
conversion step. Resulting masks export as PNG via the converter (or via the
LS Brush export endpoint).

Brush size: 5 px is good for yardlines; 8 px is decent for sidelines (they
often appear thicker in the source image). Adjust per-frame as needed.
-->
<View>
  <Image name="image" value="$image" zoom="true" zoomControl="true" rotateControl="false"/>
  <BrushLabels name="lines" toName="image">
    <Label value="yardline" background="#FFD700" hotkey="f"/>
    <Label value="sideline" background="#1E90FF" hotkey="g"/>
  </BrushLabels>
</View>
